# AgentMeter CLI — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- TypeScript (strict mode, ESM — `"type": "module"`)
- pnpm + pnpm workspaces + Turborepo
- Biome for linting and formatting (NOT ESLint, NOT Prettier)
- Vitest for tests
- Zod for runtime validation of all external data
- tsup for bundling
- Commander for CLI argument parsing
- Picocolors for terminal colors

## TypeScript Rules
- No `any` — use `unknown` with type guards or Zod `.safeParse()` for narrowing
- All built-in imports use `node:` protocol (`node:fs`, `node:path`, `node:os`)
- `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` is on — always guard array and record index access
- Zod schemas in `src/schemas/` are the source of truth for all external data shapes

## Defensive Parsing
- Wrap JSONL line parsing in per-line try/catch — skip malformed lines with a warning
- Use `z.catch(defaultValue)` or `z.safeParse()` for Zod validation of untrusted data
- Never assume the Claude Code JSONL format is stable — it is undocumented and may change

## Cross-Platform
- Use `node:path` and `node:os` — never hardcode `/` or `\` as path separators
- Service installation handles macOS (launchd) and Linux (systemd user services)
- Windows: print a message directing users to WSL or `watch` command manually

## Error Handling
- Never let the CLI crash with an unhandled exception
- Catch at all external boundaries: file I/O, network calls, JSON parsing
- Log errors with `logger.error()`, then continue or exit gracefully

## Testing
- Import from vitest explicitly: `import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'`
- Scanner tests use JSONL fixtures in `__tests__/fixtures/`
- API tests use `vi.stubGlobal('fetch', vi.fn())` for fetch mocking
- All tests must complete in < 10 seconds total

## Commands
```bash
pnpm build        # Build all packages via Turborepo
pnpm lint         # Biome check
pnpm lint:fix     # Biome auto-fix
pnpm typecheck    # TypeScript strict check (tsc --noEmit)
pnpm test         # Run all Vitest tests
```

## File Structure
```
packages/cli/
  src/
    index.ts          # CLI entry point (commander setup)
    commands/         # One file per command
    scanners/         # SessionScanner implementations
    services/         # API client, config, sync-state, logger, service installer
    utils/            # format, platform paths, retry
    schemas/          # Zod schemas for all external data
  __tests__/
    scanners/
    services/
    commands/
    fixtures/         # Real-shaped JSONL files for scanner tests
```
